Adds the full backend plumbing required for the DroneOpsSync Android app
(field controllers) to push flight logs without a user JWT login session.

NEW FILES
- backend/app/models/device_api_key.py
    DeviceApiKey model — stores label, SHA-256 key hash (raw key never
    persisted), is_active flag, and last_used_at timestamp.
    Table created automatically by create_all on next container start.

- backend/app/auth/device.py
    validate_device_api_key() FastAPI dependency — reads X-Device-Api-Key
    header, hashes it, looks up the hash in device_api_keys, returns 401
    for unknown or revoked keys.  Updates last_used_at on success.

- backend/app/routers/device_keys.py
    Settings router at /api/settings/device-keys (JWT-protected):
      GET    /api/settings/device-keys       — list all keys (no raw values)
      POST   /api/settings/device-keys       — generate key, return raw ONCE
      DELETE /api/settings/device-keys/{id}  — permanently revoke a key

MODIFIED FILES
- backend/app/routers/flight_library.py
    POST /api/flight-library/device-upload — identical upload processing
    to /upload but authenticated via validate_device_api_key instead of
    get_current_user.  This is the endpoint DroneOpsSync calls.

- backend/app/models/__init__.py
    Register DeviceApiKey so Base.metadata.create_all sees the table.

- backend/app/main.py
    Import and include device_keys router.

WORKFLOW
1. Admin creates a device key in Settings -> Device Access (or via API)
2. Raw key is copied once into DroneOpsSync controller Settings
3. DroneOpsSync POSTs to /api/flight-library/device-upload with the key
   in the X-Device-Api-Key header — works via Cloudflare tunnel or LAN

